Well, I have a gratuitous use of the DNS that I would like
some feedback on.

Users tend to be organized in many the same ways that hosts
are organized with respect to usage and administration.

I would like to consider a means whereby something very
much like nicname or whois can be done via the DNS.

This would be something like recursive resolution, since
the client would ask the (root?) server(s), which would ask
the servers authorative for lower layers (repeated N times),
passing any answers back up to the original (root?) server,
which would pass it back to the client.

Of course, doing a "whois Jones" might cause a bit of
traffic...

Anyway, does this seem reasonable?  What do `they' have to
say?

Thanks for any ideas/comments,

-Philip

